 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubrechtbertolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brecht Bertolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 677<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/28/02 6:01:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3440.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on pickup raids.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> oh please mighty brecht, delevel and lead raids for us again. NOONE could ever in the future lead raids as well as you and your list did. please o please help us all out.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lets break it down to the facts shall we.<br>
<br>
Back in the day, a year ago.....Those raid leaders were named in order the time they lead. We all learned from Each other in one way or another in that way listed.<br>
<br>
Out of all those names listed, there was not one, NOT ONE, Naggy raid failed. With Vox, out of those names (Raid leaders in order might I state again) had one Vox failure.<br>
<br>
I have been on 7 Naggy raids and 8 Vox raids since then. Naggy has failed 3 times and Vox failed 5 times. I'm just saying, the raiders/raid leaders aren't what they used to be. I'm not just talking about myself too much...I'm the most weak on the list, but the rest of the named, are better raid leaders than the ones of today.<br>
<br>
It was rare to see a failed old world dragon raid, now adays, it's common to see a failed raid. I'm not saying names, because there are good ones out there still.In General, it has all gone downhill in the last year or so.<br>
<br>
