<br>
I just have one thing to add.  Running these raids often cost 420 plat in peridots.  I know that if someone didn't get a symbol, that someone would bitch.  And if they were asked to pay for their symbol, they would bitch.  Every raid my guild has led on Vox and Naggy has provided the dots because we reserved an epic piece.  Usually we have had to lead around 10 on Vox and 10 on Naggy before the epic piece dropped.  So not only does the leader spend all the time and hassle getting things organized, he spends over 4k running them.  I think, along with all the previous arguments,  this should be considered when you bitch about a reserved piece.  Also, we only reserved one epic piece per drop, ie red scale OR pally book, never both.  Also for those of you who have said that you don't have the time to lead raids or can't commit to leading because of other issues, consider that those who are willing to work harder to get their epic pieces perhaps deserve them more than you and that they and their guild will get more benefit from having their epics than you.  This is NOT to say that RL shouldn't take precedence.  I pity those who value EQ time more than RL time, but it is just another point.<br>
